The town hall, where important meetings and community events take place.
The general store, where residents can purchase goods and supplies.
The blacksmith's forge, where the town's smith creates and repairs tools and weapons.
The inn, where travelers can rest and have a meal.
The stable, where residents can board their horses and other livestock.
The temple, where the town's inhabitants can worship and seek spiritual guidance.
The apothecary, where the town's healer prepares and dispenses medicinal herbs and remedies.
The town watch barracks, where the town's guards and protectors reside.
The farmer's market, where locals sell their crops and produce to the townspeople and visitors.
The schoolhouse, where the town's children receive an education.